  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Nutrition Intervention in 10 Woredas of Arsi Zone, Oromia Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">While Arsi zone is usually the wheat basket of Ethiopia, it has been severely hit by the El-Nino induced drought of 2016 and most woredas of the zone have been declared hotspot 1 or hotspot 2 in April 2016. As the zone is usually a food secure area, nutrition assistance to the zonal health office has been limited and there are serious capacity gaps to respond to the current nutrition situation. ACF proposes to support 10 woredas of Arsi zone with a CMAM intervention including support to the OTPs, to the stabilization center and to IYCF promotion. TSFP will take place in the 6 most affected woredas (Gololcha, Robe, Seru, Dodota- hotspot 1, and Amigna, and Chole - hotspot 2) out of the 10 supported woredas. 
The 10 woredas ACF proposes to support are: Gololcha, Robe, Seru and Dodota (hotspot 1), Amigna, Chole, Bale Gesgar, Tena, Tiyo and H/Wabe (hotspot 2). The woreda have been selected in collaboration with ENCU, Regional ENCU and the Regional Health Bureau.
The project also includes a WASH component focusing on the access to water for  25 health structuresin Arsi zone . Priority will be given to the health centers/stabilization centers). In addition it will provide point of use water treatment chemicals (POUWTC) for the nutrition beneficiaries in the five most affected woredas of Arsi.</narrative>
  </description>
